    <method>
      <name DesignerName="Initialize">_initialize</name>
      <comment>Initializes the object. 
Event is the name of the class object.
size is the width and height of the view, always a square.
Vertices is the array of vertices, defined in a type Vertice3D, example:
   vert.x = Array As Float(2, 2, 2, 2,-2,-2,-2,-2)
   vert.y = Array As Float(2, 2,-2,-2, 2, 2,-2,-2)
   vert.z = Array As Float(2,-2,-2, 2, 2,-2,-2, 2)
Polygons() is a string array, each item holds the order of vertices' number in a polygon, in a clockwise order when looking into the body's center, example:
   pol(0) = "3,2,1,0" 
   pol(1) = "2,6,5,1"
   pol(2) = "6,7,4,5"
   pol(3) = "0,4,7,3"
   pol(4) = "0,1,5,4"
   pol(5) = "2,3,7,6"
color() is array of the n polygons colors.
perspective - use around 0.03 - 0.15, changes the perspective of the body from low to high.</comment>
      <returntype>String</returntype>
      <parameter>
        <name>ba</name>
        <type>anywheresoftware.b4a.BA</type>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>Size</name>
        <type>float</type>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>Vertices</name>
        <type>derez.body3d2.body3d._vertice3d</type>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>Polygons</name>
        <type>String[]</type>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>Color</name>
        <type>int[]</type>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>Perspective</name>
        <type>float</type>
      </parameter>
    </method>
